Package: coconots
Type: Package
Title: Convolution-Closed Models for Count Time Series
Version: 1.0
Date: 2022-4-28
Author: Manuel Huth [aut,cre],
	Robert C. Jung [aut],
	A. R. Tremanye [aut]
Maintainer: Manuel Huth <manuel.huth@yahoo.com>
Description: Useful tools for fitting, validating, and forecasting of practical convolution-closed time series models for low counts are provided. Equi-dispersed and over-dispersed marginal distributions of the data can be modeled via Poisson and Generalized Poisson innovations. Regression effects can be modelled via time varying innovation rates.
Imports:
    Rcpp,
    forecast,
    numDeriv,
    HMMpa,
    stats,
    ggplot2,
    utils,
    matrixStats,
    JuliaConnectoR
LazyData: true
LinkingTo: Rcpp, StanHeaders (>= 2.21.0), RcppParallel (>= 5.0.1)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Depends: 
    R (>= 2.10)
Suggests: 
    covr,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
